
[1]equitant

   EQ'UITANT, a. [L. equitans, equito, to ride, from eques, a horseman, or
   equus, a horse.]

   In botany, riding, as equitant leaves: a term of leafing or foliation,
   when two opposite leaves converge so with their edges, that one
   incloses the other; or when the inner leaves are inclosed by the outer
   ones.
